The special option -- means "end of options" to every POSIX command except echo and test, and to many other commands. E.g. «mv -- *.png /somedir» (in case one of the filenames begins with "-"). See <http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/basedefs/V1_chap12.html#tag_12_02> and <http://wiki.bash-hackers.org/dict/terms/end_of_options>